# OrretCrypt

**Post-Quantum Ready Encryption** — Simple, secure, for everyone.

OrretCrypt encrypts files with hybrid X25519 ECDH + AES-256-GCM. The `.orret` format is versioned to support post-quantum KEMs (Kyber-768) when Python libraries mature — without changing the file format.

```
# Encrypt
python3 -m orretcrypt encrypt --key pub.pem --file document.pdf

# Decrypt
python3 -m orretcrypt decrypt --key priv.pem --file document.pdf.orret
```

## Why OrretCrypt

| | OrretCrypt | age | GPG | BitLocker |
|-|-----------|-----|-----|-----------|
| Hybrid PQC-ready | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Format: `.orret` | ✅ | `.age` | `.gpg` | proprietary |
| Web app | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Python lib | ✅ | partial | ✅ | ❌ |
| Zero-config | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ | n/a |
| IND-CCA2 secure | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |

## Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/orretter/orretcrypt
cd orretcrypt
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install cryptography
```

Or use the **web version** directly at [orretcrypt.dev](https://orretcrypt.dev) — fully offline capable.

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Generate a key pair
python3 -m orretcrypt keygen --dir ~/keys

# 2. Encrypt a file (recipient needs your public key)
python3 -m orretcrypt encrypt --key ~/keys/orretpub.pem --file report.pdf

# 3. Share the .orret file securely

# 4. Decrypt (you need your private key)
python3 -m orretcrypt decrypt --key ~/keys/orretpriv.pem --file report.pdf.orret
```

## Python API

```python
from orretcrypt import KeyPair, encrypt_file, decrypt_file

# Generate
kp = KeyPair.generate()
kp.save_public("pub.pem")
kp.save_private("priv.pem")

# Encrypt / Decrypt
encrypt_file(kp.public_key, "doc.pdf", "doc.pdf.orret")
decrypt_file(kp.private_key, "doc.pdf.orret", "doc.pdf")

# Info without decrypting
from orretcrypt import info
meta = info("doc.pdf.orret")
print(meta["kem"])  # "X25519 (ECDH)"
```

## Security

- **IND-CCA2 secure** — Hybrid encryption: ECDH key exchange + AES-256-GCM
- **Authenticated encryption** — AES-GCM provides both confidentiality and integrity
- **HKDF-SHA-512** — NIST standard key derivation
- **Pure Web Crypto** — Browser version uses native APIs, nothing leaves your device
- **Format versioned** — Ready for ML-KEM-768 (Kyber) post-quantum KEM when libs are available

## Architecture

```
.orret file format (v1)
├── magic     4 bytes   — "ORRE" (0x4F 0x52 0x52 0x45)
├── version   1 byte    — 0x01
├── kem_type  1 byte    — 0x01 (X25519) | 0x02 (Kyber-768)
├── ephem_pub 32 bytes  — Ephemeral public key (ECDH)
├── nonce     12 bytes  — AES-GCM nonce
└── ciphertext N bytes  — AES-256-GCM ciphertext + 16-byte tag
```

